AI Image Detection Survey

This survey tests your ability to spot AI modifications in images. It takes about 3-5 minutes to complete.

We do not collect any personal information, and all responses are anonymous.

Survey Instructions

You will view 5 images that have been modified by AI. For each image:

  • Shade the areas you think have been altered dragging to draw.
  • You can select multiple areas if needed.
  • Click 'Submit Mask' to move to the next image.
  • Use 'Undo' to remove your last mark if needed.
  • Here is an example:

Next Steps: Real or AI-Modified?

In this part, you will complete two tasks:

Task 1: You will view 5 images, one at a time. For each image, guess whether it is real or AI-modified by clicking the appropriate button.

Task 2: You will view 5 pairs of images. Each pair includes an image and its Grad-CAM explanation. Again, guess whether the main image is real or AI-modified.

About Grad-CAM: Grad-CAM highlights areas the AI model focuses on to judge if an image is AI-modified. Warmer colors (like red or yellow) show regions the model thinks contribute most to an AI-generated appearance. However, this is nuancedyou may see warmer colors in real images too, as the models focus isnt always perfect. Use the Grad-CAM as a guide, but trust your judgment!
